  <sect1>
    <title>Introduction</title>

    <para>Pingus is a free Lemmings(tm) clone for GNU/Linux, Win32
      and other operating systems supported by ClanLib. It is covered
      under the GPLv2, check the file COPYING, for more informations.
    </para>
    <para>See `INSTALL' for instructions on how to compile and run
      Pingus from source. If you are using the static binary have a
      look at the file README.binary. You might also want to read the
      file `FAQ' if you have throuble getting things to work.
    </para>
    <para>
      Music for the game is seperatly available at the Pingus web page.
    </para>
    <para>
      If you want to help developing Pingus, have a look on its web
      page:
    </para>
      <itemizedlist>
	<listitem><para>
	  <ulink url="http://pingus.seul.org">http://www.pingus.cx</ulink>
	  </para></listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    <para>
      for up to date informations.
    </para>
  </sect1>
  
  <sect1>
    <title>Mailing Lists</title>
    <para>
      There exist currently four mailing lists for Pingus (announce,
      users, developers and cvs), for information on how to subscribe to
      any of this list have a look at:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para>
	  <ulink url="http://pingus.seul.org">http://pingus.seul.org/contact.html
	  </ulink></para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </sect1>

  <sect1>
    <title>Bug Reports</title>
    <para>
      Questions about the game and bug reports should go to Ingo
      Ruhnke <email>grumbel@gmx.de</email> or even better one of the mailing
      lists.
    </para>
  </sect1>
